<br>
In addition, insurance companies usually include uninsured and under insured motorist coverage on the policy.  Unless your sister specifically rejected these she can try to pursue those to the full coverage limits.  (I believe the minimum in texas is 25/50 so shed be eligible for at least 25K though not a lot in the scheme of things.)<br>
<br>
If the 20 year old had insurance, she needs to get a good attorney to also pursue the coverage limits to the max on his policy.  Hopefully he was on his parents insurance, and hopefully they had higher than minimum coverage.  If you have any questions, ask.  I have been in the insurance business a while, as has Qilnyar, as well as 3 of your guild mates.  (wont say their names here in case they dont wanna admit) Maybe we can help.<br>
<br>
Stuff like this is why I cringe every time I get a call from a 18-20yr old asking for insurance. And they wonder why it was so high = (<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.dol.gov/esa/whd/fmla/">www.dol.gov/esa/whd/fmla/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
