<br>
Now parents that own assets/houses/properties etc usually have the 100/300 and up.  Nandarie, if hes insured on their policy, have her investigate as to whether or not they have an umbrella policy as well.  That covers usually catastrophic occurences and usually starting in the 1million +<br>
<br>
FMLA wont get her paid, but it will at least force the employer to admit that they were wrong, and force them to pay the amount of accrued sick/vacation time in addition to keeping her benefits active and valid for 12 weeks required by the Federal govt.<br>
