they were aware of the problem, and it was the reason for the accident. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arryalyse>Arry Alyse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Tavern's most flamed female</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(9/6/03 3:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3528.topic&index=31>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Accidents etc.</span><hr size=1> Thats true.  I read a claim once where the city of Palo Alto had to pay this childs parents 650K because the curve of the road with &quot;historic trees&quot; blocked a hairpin turn.  A 4 year old happened to run out in the street and even though the insured was going 10miles around the curve, the child amassed injuries in excess of 500K due to lung, spleen and several broken bones.  <br>
