<br>
In texas first offense $500, license suspension.  Second is $500, Vehicle impounded and suspension.  third offense mandatory 90 days in penal facility and 1 year suspension.  Unfortch they usually get released due to overcrowding.  All cases require &quot;Sr-22&quot; which the insurance co reporting when you cancel for whatever reason.  State hunts you down with an &quot;SR-26&quot;  90% of time the penalty is just another suspension.  We are far too lenient on repeat offenders.  As long as they pay their fines, and reinstatement fees, they are allowed to get away with it.  I am licensed to sell ins in 39 states, so I see and hear a lot.<br>
